<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-370-992  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 370 992.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Digital Review  June 19 1989 v6 n24 p30(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Such a deal. (Adapso objects to DEC's bundling of Rdb with itsother systems software) (editorial)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Fegreus, Jack.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Digital Equipment Corp. (marketing).andO;Ticker:    DEC.andO;Topic:     Legal IssuesRelational DBMSData Base Management SystemsAssociation of Data Processing Service Organizations.andO;Feature:   illustrationcartoon.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Such a DealandM;Psst, want to buy a real full-featured DBMS for $700?andP;  No, not a primitivedata management tool, but a real OLTP-class system.andP;  OK, you're right, thereis one small catch: no SQL and no pre-compilers to embed database accesscalls in 3GL programs.andP;  But who uses SQL as a primary database access vehicleanyway?andM;That bid for your DBMS dollars sounds a lot like the pitch used by theStreet-corner entrepreneurs of ersatz Rolex watches when not supplementingtheir income with a game of Three Card Monte.andP;  But unlike these watches,which  are guaranteed to decompose in six months, this is a database to buildlong-term applications upon.andP;  And this vendor does not supplement its incomewith high-risk games of chance, but rather with high-powered computersystems.andM;So why has Adapso, the computer software and services industry association,reacted to what DEC is doing with Rdb the way a neighborhood associationwould react if it had just seen a crack dealer set up shop?andP;  The answer isbest understood once you know the power of what DEC is selling with--orbundling into--the VMS operating system by including a Runtime Rdb license.andM;When DEC announced the inclusion of Runtime Rdb with VMS, the move soundedbenign.andP;  Runtime Rdb would simply serve as a deployment platform on which todistribute completed, ready-to-run, Rdb-based applications.andM;But that's not all you get, and there's the rub.andP;  Once you purchase the mediaand documentation set, you discover that you have a very robust and virtuallycomplete relational database management system.andP;  Want to create and querytables?andP;  No problem--especially if you're an old Datatrieve hacker.andP;  Usingthe Relational Database Operator, which is included in Runtime RDB, you arefree to do all of these things.andP;  Those who need more can always add a4GL--relatively in-expensive compared with the price of a full-blown RDBMS.andM;That is why there is a great hue and cry from Adapso that DEC is engaging inunfair business practices and predatory pricing by bundling products like Rdband PCSA with its other systems software.andP;  That is why there are threats toseek support from the Justice Department.andP;  Does Adapso have a case?andP;  Well, asone user of a third-party database who is facing a $20,000 license charge toupgrade to a MicroVAX 3900, I must admit that DEC's deal is looking betterand better.andM;But the downside of this immediate windfall, both for users and for DEC, maywell be a migration of the best and most innovative software developers outof the DEC market.andP;  In its rush for additional revenue, DEC had best takecare that it doesn't kill the goose that laid the golden egg.andO;</TEXT></DOC>